High altitude can lead to an oxygen debt.. especially when one is pursued frequently by bears...protoplasm begins to collapse in the brain cells..strange behaviors evolve.. like triple posting!  More serious cases.. usually seen among fighter pilots can lead to severe slobbering or fraternization with cannon cockers.<br>
Most recover unless the condition is aggravated by a previous history of crawling through small tunnels.. chasing chickens...Why didn't you just go on R&amp;R?<br>
If the condition persists...put on some Shepard Ballads and get lost in a bottle of Woolite with a Koolaid back...forget about the chicken.<br><br>
